700078f-a.text:
East 139th Street, west from and including Brook Ave., showing W.P.A. men working on a sewer project. Slightly west of the S.W. corner of Brook Ave. is visible Public School No. 9, and in the background appears part of the Third Ave. elevated line running between
Willis and Alexander Aves.
September 3, 1936.
Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project.
